I am loathe to review chains but this place deserves their rating for the ineptitude and behavior. Customer Service is appalling since they don't understand the meaning of keeping orders timely. I had to wait ten whole minutes for my order after paying. While the folks in the back were goofing around, no attempt was made to appraise me of the status of my order, a simple chicken sandwich combo listed front and center on the board. If that didn't put a damper on my day, the food tasted like crap.  Contrary to popular belief, not all BK taste and run alike. I will definitely not be coming back. If you do, go to Popeye's in the adjoining area.

My experience with BK in Long island was always good so for nostalgia sake I tried this BK since it's in my nabe and this has been my experience:  The first time I was there, I had to witness a middle-aged female employee being harassed by her male co-workers Pakistani style. She even complained to the owner but the male co-workers kept at it. My order was right, the workspace and the workers were gross, except the ones at the cash registers.  The second time I went there it was same old same old with the Pakistani crew fooling around while running an operation. No female staff this time around but guess what? My fries were only half filled. My guess is the owner and the staff are petty besides being gross. Bay Ridge does NOT deserve this kind of service. Anyone eating here, please be warned. Do not patronize this franchise. It's a waste of your money and time. This Burger King in Bay Ridge is half Popeyes. They share the same space. I went in to get the original chicken sandwich and it was not as good as I remember it. They also have a chicken Philly cheesesteak which I find hilarious. Try out the fancy soda machine. 50 cent cones are the best thing here.
Any of you getting food to go, please check before you leave. The staff has this wonderful habit of giving you less than what you ordered.
